%N A394088 Decimal expansion of 1/zeta(2)^2 + Sum_{k>=2} k * ((1/zeta(k)-1/zeta(k+1))^2).
%C A394088 The asymptotic mean of the common maximum exponent in the prime factorizations of two positive integers selected independently at random, defined as 0 if their maximum exponents differ.
%C A394088 The asymptotic mean over the pairs with a common maximum exponent is this constant divided by A393778, i.e., 1.17180286212502644048... .
%e A394088 0.504218883262417684726585962603297309097398961445386...
%o A394088 (PARI) 1/zeta(2)^2 + sumpos(k = 2, k * (1/zeta(k)-1/zeta(k+1))^2)
